<TITLE> Suspected mugger beaten to death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 2 (bdnews24.com)  A young man suspected of being a mugger was beaten to death by a mob in south Keraniganj on Saturday night. Mohammad Ali, sub-inspector of the south Keraniganj said that 25-year old Shukkur Ali was well known as a mugger in the locality. He told bdnews24.com that three youths were "taking preparation for a robbery" in front of a school at around 11pm. Local people chased them, caught hold of two of them and beat them up. Shukkur died on the spot and another one Momin, 20, was taken to the police station after receiving first aid, Ali said. One of the three youths escaped. bd
